1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:55,260
Reverse Mountain

3
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:10,070
What's wrong, Zoro?

4
00:02:10,070 --> 00:02:12,570
You've had a serious look
on your face for a while.

5
00:02:12,570 --> 00:02:15,110
Well, I might just be
imagining things, but...

6
00:02:15,110 --> 00:02:16,070
But what?

7
00:02:16,070 --> 00:02:20,700
I feel like the ship
hasn't moved in a while.

8
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:25,540
What?

9
00:02:26,630 --> 00:02:30,920
Now that you mention it,
the sail isn't catching any wind...

10
00:02:34,340 --> 00:02:35,470
Oh no...!

11
00:02:35,470 --> 00:02:37,550
We've entered the Calm Belt!

12
00:02:37,890 --> 00:02:38,890
The Balm Belt?

13
00:02:38,890 --> 00:02:39,720
The heck is that?

14
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:42,230
The Calm Belt! A sea where
nothing moves a muscle!

15
00:02:42,230 --> 00:02:43,310
You grew some muscle?

16
00:02:43,310 --> 00:02:44,520
No, you idiot!

17
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,610
Was that an earthquake?

18
00:02:52,610 --> 00:02:54,400
An earthquake? But we're at sea.

19
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:56,820
Come on, guys, focus!

20
00:02:56,820 --> 00:02:58,740
Hoist the sails and start paddling!

21
00:02:58,740 --> 00:03:00,330
Put the ship back on course, now!

22
00:03:00,330 --> 00:03:01,700
As you wish, Nami!

23
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,960
What are you panicking about?

24
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,790
And why paddle? This is a sailboat.

25
00:03:05,790 --> 00:03:06,960
Yeah, why?

26
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:09,790
Just shut up and do as I say!
We're in big trouble!

27
00:03:09,790 --> 00:03:11,630
But the sea is nice and quiet here.

28
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:12,260
Yeah.

29
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:15,010
Alright, fine! I'll explain!

30
00:03:15,010 --> 00:03:20,600
Listen. Since we were in such a hurry,
we went farther south than intended!

31
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,520
So we're in the Grand Line now?

32
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:24,140
Alright!

33
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:27,150
If it was that easy,
anyone could enter!

34
00:03:28,730 --> 00:03:29,730
Look here.

35
00:03:29,730 --> 00:03:34,690
The Grand Line runs between
these two strips of sea.

36
00:03:34,690 --> 00:03:39,530
Are you following? The two strips
are called the Calm Belts.

37
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:44,870
The reason's unknown, but no wind
or currents flow through them.

38
00:03:44,870 --> 00:03:46,910
These seas are completely calm.

39
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:49,670
Sailboats need wind to move
so it's very dangerous—

40
00:03:49,670 --> 00:03:51,420
maybe even fatal—without it!

41
00:03:51,420 --> 00:03:52,920
Did you get all that, Luffy?

42
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:54,710
Yeah. Basically, we're in trouble.

43
00:03:54,710 --> 00:03:57,430
That explains the lack of wind.

44
00:03:57,430 --> 00:03:59,760
Not much we can do
if the ship can't move.

45
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:01,510
Can't we just wait for wind to–

46
00:04:01,510 --> 00:04:05,640
I just explained this! Wind won't blow
no matter how long you wait here!

47
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:06,810
And that's not all!

48
00:04:06,810 --> 00:04:10,190
There's another reason
this area is dangerous!

49
00:04:10,190 --> 00:04:11,610
The Calm Belt is–

50
00:04:13,610 --> 00:04:15,070
What's going on?

51
00:04:20,490 --> 00:04:22,160
They're here!

52
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:23,410
Huh?

53
00:04:23,410 --> 00:04:24,200
What's that?

54
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,790
Th-Th-They're...

55
00:04:31,790 --> 00:04:33,590
They're huge!

56
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:42,550
The Calm Belt is a nest of sea kings.

57
00:04:42,550 --> 00:04:44,510
Specifically colossal ones.

58
00:04:44,890 --> 00:04:48,980
They're the other reason people
can't cross the Calm Belt...

59
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:51,900
What do we do now?

60
00:04:52,270 --> 00:04:55,270
F-For the time being, no one move.

61
00:04:55,270 --> 00:04:57,400
They'll go back into
the sea eventually.

62
00:04:57,400 --> 00:05:00,910
When they do, we paddle
as hard as possible.

63
00:05:00,910 --> 00:05:02,660
Are you serious?!

64
00:05:02,660 --> 00:05:03,530
Shut it, idiot!

65
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,120
Sorry...

66
00:05:11,540 --> 00:05:13,210
Hold on a sec...!

67
00:05:13,210 --> 00:05:14,670
If it does that...

68
00:05:14,670 --> 00:05:17,170
He's gonna sneeze!

69
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:20,050
– What?!
– What?!

70
00:05:20,050 --> 00:05:22,800
Wow! It feels like we're flying!

71
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:31,190
We are flying!

72
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:36,400
Looks like we're back on course...

73
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:39,940
We should be seeing
the Red Line any moment now.

74
00:05:43,950 --> 00:05:46,990
Are we finally going
into the Grand Line?!

75
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:52,080
Hey, Sanji! We're here,
we're here, we're finally here!

76
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:53,670
That hurts!

77
00:05:53,670 --> 00:05:54,750
Sorry...

78
00:05:55,210 --> 00:05:56,460
Zoro!

79
00:05:56,460 --> 00:05:57,710
We're here, we're here!
But...

80
00:05:57,710 --> 00:06:01,340
We're here, we're here, we're here!
is the drawing an accurate
representation of what we'll find?

81
00:06:01,340 --> 00:06:03,470
Quit it!

82
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:10,180
Look at this!

83
00:06:11,430 --> 00:06:15,100
I'd heard the rumors about it,
and it's drawn on this map, too!

84
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:19,150
If all of that is true, then the entrance
to the Grand Line is a mountain!

85
00:06:19,150 --> 00:06:20,690
A mountain?

86
00:06:20,690 --> 00:06:22,070
We gotta crash into it?

87
00:06:22,070 --> 00:06:23,200
You're kidding, right?

88
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:28,200
I doubted it myself, but the map
shows canals leading to the mountain.

89
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:30,370
That might mean we have to go up it!

90
00:06:31,450 --> 00:06:33,250
Cool!

91
00:06:33,250 --> 00:06:34,710
What are you talking about?!

92
00:06:34,710 --> 00:06:39,090
Even with canals or whatever,
a ship can't climb up a mountain!

93
00:06:39,090 --> 00:06:40,710
But that's what the map says!

94
00:06:40,710 --> 00:06:44,180
Exactly! Nami would never
say anything wrong!

95
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:47,430
You stole that map
from Buggy, right?

96
00:06:47,430 --> 00:06:48,850
Can we really trust it?

97
00:06:48,850 --> 00:06:50,140
H-Hey!

98
00:06:50,140 --> 00:06:52,180
Someone help me move the whipstaff!

99
00:06:52,180 --> 00:06:54,560
Sanji! Give Usopp a hand!

100
00:06:52,770 --> 00:06:55,560
It won't budge!

101
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:56,900
I can't think with all his shouting!

102
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:58,440
It won't move! Someone help!

103
00:06:56,900 --> 00:06:58,440
Right away, Nami!

104
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:59,520
Here I go!

105
00:06:59,980 --> 00:07:03,440
D-Doesn't this current
seem a bit strong?!

106
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:04,200
Huh?

107
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:05,820
Usopp, say that again!

108
00:07:05,820 --> 00:07:08,570
"D-Doesn't this current
seem a bit strong?!"

109
00:07:08,570 --> 00:07:10,370
Current...

110
00:07:10,370 --> 00:07:11,200
That's it!

111
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,330
What's it?

112
00:07:12,330 --> 00:07:14,160
The canals do go up the mountain!

113
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:16,710
You're still on that?

114
00:07:16,710 --> 00:07:17,420
Look here!

115
00:07:17,420 --> 00:07:18,540
See?

116
00:07:18,540 --> 00:07:21,750
The guiding light was
definitely pointing to here.

117
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:24,090
Right on the Red Line:
Reverse Mountain!

118
00:07:24,090 --> 00:07:26,550
Hey! What do I do now?!

119
00:07:27,090 --> 00:07:29,220
See these canals here?

120
00:07:29,220 --> 00:07:34,680
If major currents from the four seas
all flowed toward this mountain...

121
00:07:36,020 --> 00:07:40,270
Then the four currents would go up
these canals, collide at the top,

122
00:07:40,270 --> 00:07:42,360
and flow into the Grand Line!

123
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:45,070
Reverse Mountain is a winter island,

124
00:07:45,070 --> 00:07:50,410
so any currents that collide with
the Red Line will go into the depths.

125
00:07:50,410 --> 00:07:53,040
If we screw up and miss
the entrance to the canal...

126
00:07:53,660 --> 00:07:56,500
the Going Merry will crash
into the Red Line...

127
00:07:58,750 --> 00:08:00,920
and get completely wrecked!

128
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:04,300
Then we'd end up at the bottom
of the ocean. Get it?

129
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:05,720
Oh, very interesting!

130
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:08,760
So, basically, it's a mystery mountain!

131
00:08:10,140 --> 00:08:13,060
Well, I guess you wouldn't...

132
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,680
All in all, now that
we're on this current,

133
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:18,440
as long as we steer correctly,

134
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:21,650
it's a straight shot to the summit
of Reverse Mountain!

135
00:08:21,650 --> 00:08:24,530
You're amazing, Nami!

136
00:08:24,530 --> 00:08:27,450
I've never heard of someone
going up a mountain by boat.

137
00:08:27,450 --> 00:08:29,160
I've heard some stories!

138
00:08:29,530 --> 00:08:30,950
About the mystery mountain?

139
00:08:30,950 --> 00:08:32,070
No.

140
00:08:32,580 --> 00:08:37,710
I heard that half of everyone who heads
to the Grand Line die before entering...

141
00:08:38,660 --> 00:08:41,630
I knew getting in wouldn't be easy.

142
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,500
Sanji! Could you get the sail?

143
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:45,250
Of course, Nami!

144
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:46,380
Luffy! Help out!

145
00:08:46,380 --> 00:08:48,340
What?!

146
00:09:00,730 --> 00:09:01,980
Hey!

147
00:09:01,980 --> 00:09:04,110
I see the mystery mountain!

148
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:05,730
– Wh-What?!
– What?!

149
00:09:06,150 --> 00:09:08,780
Th-That's insanely huge!

150
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:13,740
So that's the Red Line, huh?!

151
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:20,250
Th-Th-The t-top's all the way
above the clouds!

152
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:42,480
We're getting sucked in!

153
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:44,730
Hold the rudder tight!

154
00:09:44,730 --> 00:09:46,230
– On it!
– On it!

155
00:09:53,530 --> 00:09:56,120
N-Nami! Wh-Where's the entrance?!

156
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:59,080
We're gonna crash
if we keep going this way!

157
00:10:01,410 --> 00:10:03,330
The crack in that cliff...

158
00:10:06,210 --> 00:10:09,050
Nami! What do we do?!

159
00:10:09,050 --> 00:10:10,460
Keep going straight ahead!

160
00:10:10,460 --> 00:10:11,630
Are you sure?!

161
00:10:11,630 --> 00:10:12,840
Just do it!

162
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:15,800
Nami! Is that the entrance?

163
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,260
Most likely!

164
00:10:17,930 --> 00:10:19,720
I can't believe this...!

165
00:10:20,390 --> 00:10:23,890
The damn ocean really is
flowing up the mountain!

166
00:10:28,980 --> 00:10:32,240
We gotta be careful sailing
through those gates!

167
00:10:32,570 --> 00:10:35,110
If we don't get it just right,
the ship is done for!

168
00:10:38,910 --> 00:10:42,120
W-We're a little off!
More to the right! The right!

169
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:44,420
The right?! Go starboard!

170
00:10:47,210 --> 00:10:49,710
C-Come on, now!

171
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:58,180
– The whipstaff!
– The whipstaff!

172
00:10:58,180 --> 00:11:00,890
Gum-Gum Balloon!

173
00:11:11,730 --> 00:11:13,490
Luffy!

174
00:11:13,940 --> 00:11:14,820
Grab on!

175
00:11:27,710 --> 00:11:30,380
– We made it!
– We made it!

176
00:11:36,510 --> 00:11:39,850
Now it's just a straight
shot to the summit!

177
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:46,850
A-Awesome!

178
00:11:54,110 --> 00:11:55,190
Awesome, right?

179
00:11:57,300 --> 00:12:00,070
We're in the clouds!

180
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,340
So cool!

181
00:12:14,760 --> 00:12:16,840
Now we're above the clouds!

182
00:12:27,180 --> 00:12:30,270
Look! It's the summit! The summit!

183
00:12:43,030 --> 00:12:45,290
Yahoo!

184
00:13:06,390 --> 00:13:07,430
I see it!

185
00:13:07,850 --> 00:13:10,270
This is the greatest sea in the world!

186
00:13:10,270 --> 00:13:11,560
The Grand Line!

187
00:13:14,270 --> 00:13:18,610
The One Piece is somewhere up ahead!

188
00:13:19,190 --> 00:13:21,740
Go!

189
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:38,130
Did you hear that just now?

190
00:13:38,130 --> 00:13:40,050
Wasn't it just the wind?

191
00:13:40,050 --> 00:13:43,220
It must be from all the weird
landforms around here.

192
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:49,480
What's that?

193
00:13:50,060 --> 00:13:52,560
Nami! I see a mountain up ahead!

194
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:54,900
A mountain?! That can't be right!

195
00:13:54,900 --> 00:13:56,940
But there's really one there!

196
00:13:56,940 --> 00:13:59,230
Who cares?! Go!

197
00:13:59,900 --> 00:14:03,910
It should be open sea once
we pass the Twin Capes up ahead!

198
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:11,120
Oh, crap!

199
00:14:13,290 --> 00:14:14,750
It's not a mountain!

200
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:16,000
It's a big black wall!

201
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,170
No, it's not! That's...

202
00:14:17,170 --> 00:14:18,300
What is it then?!

203
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:19,550
I-I-I-It's...

204
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:21,670
It's a whale!

205
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:25,680
Wh-Wh-What are we g-gonna do?!

206
00:14:25,680 --> 00:14:26,640
We should fight it!

207
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:28,810
Are you crazy?! How are
we gonna fight that?!

208
00:14:28,810 --> 00:14:31,770
B-B-But, i-i-it's blocking our way!

209
00:14:31,770 --> 00:14:33,480
What are we gonna do?!

210
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:34,940
Hold on a sec!

211
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:39,440
If it looks like a wall from
this close, where are its eyes?!

212
00:14:39,940 --> 00:14:43,570
That's right! Maybe it
hasn't noticed us yet!

213
00:14:43,570 --> 00:14:46,120
Either way, we're about
to crash into it!

214
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:48,160
Hey! There's an opening on the left!

215
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:50,620
Port! Hard to port!

216
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,700
But the whipstaff is broken!

217
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:55,170
Well, figure something out! I'll help!

218
00:14:55,170 --> 00:14:56,540
Oh, yeah!

219
00:14:56,540 --> 00:14:58,840
I've got an idea!

220
00:14:58,840 --> 00:14:59,500
Luffy...?

221
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:01,380
Hey, what are you doing?!

222
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,550
This isn't working!

223
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:11,140
The ship won't turn!

224
00:15:11,140 --> 00:15:12,430
Dammit!

225
00:15:12,430 --> 00:15:14,560
Don't give up!

226
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:25,150
Is this it...?!

227
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:34,370
The cannon?!

228
00:15:32,410 --> 00:15:34,370
The cannon?!

229
00:15:32,660 --> 00:15:34,370
The cannon?!

230
00:15:32,910 --> 00:15:34,370
The cannon?!

231
00:15:34,370 --> 00:15:36,330
Alright! Did it stop?

232
00:15:44,340 --> 00:15:45,420
We're screwed...

233
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:46,840
Yeah, this is it...

234
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:51,600
My special seat!

235
00:16:08,660 --> 00:16:09,240
Let's...

236
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:11,160
Let's book it while we still can!

237
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:13,160
What the heck is going on?!

238
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:15,660
Is it so big that
it didn't even feel it?!

239
00:16:15,660 --> 00:16:17,000
Or is it just slow?!

240
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,960
Who cares?! Let's get
the hell out of here!

241
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:25,840
My ears!

242
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:27,470
Paddle! Just keep paddling!

243
00:16:27,470 --> 00:16:29,380
We have to get away from it!

244
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:36,730
Luffy...?

245
00:16:36,730 --> 00:16:38,100
You!

246
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:42,690
What the hell did you do
to my special seat?!

247
00:16:43,980 --> 00:16:46,990
– You dumbass!
– You dumbass!

248
00:16:53,910 --> 00:16:56,750
How was that, huh?!
Bring it on, you bastard!

249
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:58,330
– Shut up already, you idiot!
– Shut up already, you idiot!

250
00:17:02,330 --> 00:17:03,710
Wh-What?

251
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:20,600
Luffy!

252
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:21,480
Luffy!

253
00:17:27,690 --> 00:17:30,650
I'm not gonna die!

254
00:17:58,270 --> 00:17:59,600
What am I gonna do?

255
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:01,140
They all got eaten...

256
00:18:02,190 --> 00:18:05,150
Hey, you! Spit them out!
Give everyone back!

257
00:18:05,150 --> 00:18:07,070
Spit them out already! Listen to me!

258
00:18:07,070 --> 00:18:07,980
You–

259
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:11,990
You... You jerk!

260
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:14,490
Are you diving?! Stop it!

261
00:18:14,490 --> 00:18:16,950
Hey! I said stop! Hey!

262
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:19,910
Please, stop! Give my friends back!

263
00:18:20,370 --> 00:18:21,160
Hey!

264
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:22,870
Stop it already!

265
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:25,540
We were just about
to go on an adventure!

266
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:26,880
I can't lose them!

267
00:18:27,380 --> 00:18:30,010
Give them back!

268
00:18:51,530 --> 00:18:53,610
So, what do you think?

269
00:18:53,610 --> 00:18:55,530
What do I think...?

270
00:18:55,530 --> 00:18:57,240
What should I think?

271
00:18:57,240 --> 00:18:58,990
H-H-H-H-How...?

272
00:18:58,990 --> 00:19:03,160
We were definitely
swallowed by that whale...

273
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:06,580
Is this a dream?

274
00:19:06,580 --> 00:19:09,170
Yeah, it's gotta be a dream.

275
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:17,390
Then, how do you explain
that island and house?

276
00:19:17,390 --> 00:19:18,760
Hallucinations.

277
00:19:23,350 --> 00:19:25,520
So, that's also...?

278
00:19:26,190 --> 00:19:29,520
– It's an imperial squid!
– It's an imperial squid!

279
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:52,750
Looks like someone lives there.

280
00:19:52,750 --> 00:19:54,340
Let's hope they're human.

281
00:19:55,340 --> 00:19:57,340
I've had enough. I wanna go home.

282
00:19:57,340 --> 00:20:01,140
Luffy's gone, too...
What's gonna happen to us?

283
00:20:01,140 --> 00:20:02,810
You're right! Where's Luffy?!

284
00:20:04,850 --> 00:20:06,690
What the heck is all this?

285
00:20:06,690 --> 00:20:10,610
Why is there a door
to a hallway inside a whale?

286
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:14,570
A ship...

287
00:20:14,570 --> 00:20:18,740
Sh-Sh-Should we f-fire
the cannon at that island?!

288
00:20:18,740 --> 00:20:20,570
No, hold on a sec...

289
00:20:22,030 --> 00:20:24,040
Someone's coming out...
